[
  {
    "text": "Translator: Camille Mart√≠nez",
    "start": 0.0,
    "duration": 7.0
  },
  {
    "text": "The first time",
    "start": 13.518,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "I felt fear",
    "start": 15.422,
    "duration": 1.422
  },
  {
    "text": "I was 41 years old.",
    "start": 17.841,
    "duration": 1.263
  },
  {
    "text": "People have always said I was brave.",
    "start": 20.502,
    "duration": 2.414
  },
  {
    "text": "When I was little,\nI'd climb the highest tree,",
    "start": 23.499,
    "duration": 2.619
  },
  {
    "text": "and I'd approach any animal fearlessly.",
    "start": 26.142,
    "duration": 2.52
  },
  {
    "text": "I liked challenges.",
    "start": 29.821,
    "duration": 1.555
  },
  {
    "text": "My father used to say,",
    "start": 32.106,
    "duration": 1.334
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Good steel can withstand\nany temperature.\"",
    "start": 34.622,
    "duration": 4.424
  },
  {
    "text": "And when I entered into\nColombian politics,",
    "start": 40.153,
    "duration": 3.003
  },
  {
    "text": "I thought I'd be able\nto withstand any temperature.",
    "start": 44.265,
    "duration": 2.481
  },
  {
    "text": "I wanted to end corruption;",
    "start": 46.77,
    "duration": 2.171
  },
  {
    "text": "I wanted to cut ties between politicians\nand drug traffickers.",
    "start": 48.965,
    "duration": 4.179
  },
  {
    "text": "The first time I was elected,",
    "start": 53.168,
    "duration": 2.658
  },
  {
    "text": "it was because I called out, by name,",
    "start": 55.85,
    "duration": 2.683
  },
  {
    "text": "corrupt and untouchable politicians.",
    "start": 58.557,
    "duration": 3.021
  },
  {
    "text": "I also called out the president",
    "start": 62.172,
    "duration": 2.346
  },
  {
    "text": "for his ties to the cartels.",
    "start": 65.388,
    "duration": 2.91
  },
  {
    "text": "That's when the threats started.",
    "start": 69.46,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "I had to send my very young children\nout of the country one morning,",
    "start": 72.449,
    "duration": 5.332
  },
  {
    "text": "hidden, all the way to the airport,\nin the French ambassador's armored car.",
    "start": 77.805,
    "duration": 4.162
  },
  {
    "text": "Days later,",
    "start": 82.425,
    "duration": 1.38
  },
  {
    "text": "I was the victim of an attack,\nbut emerged unharmed.",
    "start": 84.742,
    "duration": 2.623
  },
  {
    "text": "The following year,",
    "start": 88.944,
    "duration": 1.323
  },
  {
    "text": "the Colombian people elected me\nwith the highest number of votes.",
    "start": 91.135,
    "duration": 3.507
  },
  {
    "text": "I thought people applauded me\nbecause I was brave.",
    "start": 95.755,
    "duration": 3.483
  },
  {
    "text": "I, too, thought I was brave.",
    "start": 100.224,
    "duration": 2.127
  },
  {
    "text": "But I wasn't.",
    "start": 103.279,
    "duration": 1.404
  },
  {
    "text": "I had simply never before experienced",
    "start": 106.714,
    "duration": 3.552
  },
  {
    "text": "true fear.",
    "start": 110.905,
    "duration": 2.24
  },
  {
    "text": "That changed",
    "start": 114.557,
    "duration": 1.176
  },
  {
    "text": "on February 23, 2002.",
    "start": 117.066,
    "duration": 2.381
  },
  {
    "text": "At the time, I was a presidential\ncandidate in Colombia",
    "start": 121.066,
    "duration": 3.28
  },
  {
    "text": "promoting my campaign agenda,",
    "start": 125.029,
    "duration": 3.348
  },
  {
    "text": "when I was detained\nby a group of armed men.",
    "start": 128.401,
    "duration": 3.233
  },
  {
    "text": "They were wearing uniforms\nwith military garments.",
    "start": 132.222,
    "duration": 2.815
  },
  {
    "text": "I looked at their boots; they were rubber.",
    "start": 136.41,
    "duration": 2.753
  },
  {
    "text": "And I knew",
    "start": 139.187,
    "duration": 1.409
  },
  {
    "text": "that the Colombian army\nwore leather boots.",
    "start": 140.62,
    "duration": 2.301
  },
  {
    "text": "I knew that these were FARC guerrillas.",
    "start": 143.767,
    "duration": 3.674
  },
  {
    "text": "From that point on,\neverything happened very quickly.",
    "start": 148.068,
    "duration": 2.73
  },
  {
    "text": "The commando leader ordered us\nto stop the vehicle.",
    "start": 153.457,
    "duration": 3.506
  },
  {
    "text": "Meanwhile, one of his men\nstepped on an antipersonnel mine",
    "start": 157.891,
    "duration": 4.131
  },
  {
    "text": "and flew through the air.",
    "start": 162.704,
    "duration": 2.124
  },
  {
    "text": "He landed, sitting upright,",
    "start": 165.574,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "right in front of me.",
    "start": 168.256,
    "duration": 1.649
  },
  {
    "text": "We made eye contact",
    "start": 169.929,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "and it was then\nthat the young man understood:",
    "start": 172.841,
    "duration": 2.349
  },
  {
    "text": "his rubber boot with his leg still in it",
    "start": 176.246,
    "duration": 2.483
  },
  {
    "text": "had landed far away.",
    "start": 178.753,
    "duration": 1.445
  },
  {
    "text": "(Sighs)",
    "start": 181.744,
    "duration": 1.19
  },
  {
    "text": "He started",
    "start": 184.823,
    "duration": 1.231
  },
  {
    "text": "screaming like crazy.",
    "start": 188.689,
    "duration": 2.253
  },
  {
    "text": "And the truth is,",
    "start": 192.972,
    "duration": 1.169
  },
  {
    "text": "I felt -- as I feel right now,\nbecause I'm reliving these emotions --",
    "start": 194.816,
    "duration": 6.144
  },
  {
    "text": "I felt at that moment\nthat something inside of me was breaking",
    "start": 200.984,
    "duration": 3.633
  },
  {
    "text": "and that I was being infected\nwith his fear.",
    "start": 205.54,
    "duration": 2.903
  },
  {
    "text": "My mind went blank and couldn't think;",
    "start": 208.467,
    "duration": 2.864
  },
  {
    "text": "it was paralyzed.",
    "start": 211.355,
    "duration": 1.175
  },
  {
    "text": "When I finally reacted,",
    "start": 213.243,
    "duration": 1.693
  },
  {
    "text": "I said to myself,",
    "start": 216.879,
    "duration": 1.459
  },
  {
    "text": "\"They're going to kill me,",
    "start": 218.716,
    "duration": 1.277
  },
  {
    "text": "and I didn't say goodbye to my children.\"",
    "start": 221.128,
    "duration": 2.341
  },
  {
    "text": "As they took me into\nthe deepest depths of the jungle,",
    "start": 226.798,
    "duration": 4.053
  },
  {
    "text": "the FARC soldiers announced",
    "start": 232.796,
    "duration": 1.607
  },
  {
    "text": "that if the government didn't negotiate,",
    "start": 235.169,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "they'd kill me.",
    "start": 238.406,
    "duration": 1.244
  },
  {
    "text": "And I knew",
    "start": 240.674,
    "duration": 1.75
  },
  {
    "text": "that the government wouldn't negotiate.",
    "start": 243.269,
    "duration": 3.152
  },
  {
    "text": "From that point on,",
    "start": 247.865,
    "duration": 1.303
  },
  {
    "text": "I went to sleep in fear every night --",
    "start": 249.898,
    "duration": 3.092
  },
  {
    "text": "cold sweats,",
    "start": 253.014,
    "duration": 1.42
  },
  {
    "text": "shaking,",
    "start": 255.039,
    "duration": 1.283
  },
  {
    "text": "stomach ache,",
    "start": 257.187,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "insomnia.",
    "start": 259.211,
    "duration": 1.257
  },
  {
    "text": "But worse than that\nwas what was happening to my mind,",
    "start": 261.793,
    "duration": 2.58
  },
  {
    "text": "because my memory was being erased:\nall the phone numbers,",
    "start": 264.397,
    "duration": 4.499
  },
  {
    "text": "addresses,",
    "start": 268.92,
    "duration": 1.487
  },
  {
    "text": "names of very dear people,",
    "start": 270.431,
    "duration": 2.069
  },
  {
    "text": "even significant life events.",
    "start": 272.524,
    "duration": 3.679
  },
  {
    "text": "And so,",
    "start": 278.386,
    "duration": 1.322
  },
  {
    "text": "I began to doubt myself,\nto doubt my mental health.",
    "start": 280.41,
    "duration": 2.984
  },
  {
    "text": "And with doubt came desperation,",
    "start": 284.862,
    "duration": 2.973
  },
  {
    "text": "and with desperation came depression.",
    "start": 288.565,
    "duration": 2.094
  },
  {
    "text": "I was suffering notorious\nbehavioral changes",
    "start": 291.787,
    "duration": 2.778
  },
  {
    "text": "and it wasn't just paranoia\nin moments of panic.",
    "start": 294.589,
    "duration": 3.627
  },
  {
    "text": "It was distrust,",
    "start": 298.969,
    "duration": 2.762
  },
  {
    "text": "it was hatred,",
    "start": 302.692,
    "duration": 1.25
  },
  {
    "text": "and it was also the urge to kill.",
    "start": 304.716,
    "duration": 1.921
  },
  {
    "text": "This, I realized",
    "start": 307.574,
    "duration": 2.267
  },
  {
    "text": "when they had me\nchained by the neck to a tree.",
    "start": 309.865,
    "duration": 4.561
  },
  {
    "text": "They kept me outside that day,",
    "start": 315.767,
    "duration": 3.287
  },
  {
    "text": "during a tropical downpour.",
    "start": 320.086,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember feeling an urgent need\nto use the bathroom.",
    "start": 323.058,
    "duration": 5.3
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Whatever you have to do,",
    "start": 332.832,
    "duration": 1.537
  },
  {
    "text": "you'll do in front of me,",
    "start": 336.616,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "bitch,\"",
    "start": 343.481,
    "duration": 1.214
  },
  {
    "text": "the guard screamed at me.",
    "start": 350.871,
    "duration": 1.539
  },
  {
    "text": "And I",
    "start": 361.121,
    "duration": 1.161
  },
  {
    "text": "decided at that moment",
    "start": 364.797,
    "duration": 2.609
  },
  {
    "text": "to kill him.",
    "start": 376.66,
    "duration": 1.233
  },
  {
    "text": "And for days,",
    "start": 382.155,
    "duration": 2.668
  },
  {
    "text": "I was planning, trying to find\nthe right moment, the right way to do it,",
    "start": 386.426,
    "duration": 4.113
  },
  {
    "text": "filled with hatred,",
    "start": 390.563,
    "duration": 1.485
  },
  {
    "text": "filled with fear.",
    "start": 392.072,
    "duration": 1.174
  },
  {
    "text": "Then suddenly,",
    "start": 393.984,
    "duration": 1.792
  },
  {
    "text": "I rose up,",
    "start": 395.8,
    "duration": 1.26
  },
  {
    "text": "snapped out of it",
    "start": 397.084,
    "duration": 1.348
  },
  {
    "text": "and thought:",
    "start": 399.209,
    "duration": 1.213
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I'm not going to become one of them.",
    "start": 401.405,
    "duration": 2.104
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm not going to become an assassin.",
    "start": 403.533,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "I still have enough freedom",
    "start": 406.47,
    "duration": 4.318
  },
  {
    "text": "to decide",
    "start": 412.756,
    "duration": 1.409
  },
  {
    "text": "who I want to be.\"",
    "start": 415.327,
    "duration": 1.394
  },
  {
    "text": "That's when I learned that fear",
    "start": 419.832,
    "duration": 1.813
  },
  {
    "text": "brought me face to face with myself.",
    "start": 424.134,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "It forced me",
    "start": 427.047,
    "duration": 1.183
  },
  {
    "text": "to align my energies,",
    "start": 429.212,
    "duration": 2.462
  },
  {
    "text": "to align my meridians.",
    "start": 431.698,
    "duration": 2.568
  },
  {
    "text": "I learned that facing fear",
    "start": 435.321,
    "duration": 2.713
  },
  {
    "text": "could become a pathway to growth.",
    "start": 439.717,
    "duration": 3.532
  },
  {
    "text": "A lot of emotions arise\nwhen I talk about all of this,",
    "start": 445.55,
    "duration": 2.698
  },
  {
    "text": "but when I think back,",
    "start": 448.938,
    "duration": 2.187
  },
  {
    "text": "I'm able to identify",
    "start": 452.601,
    "duration": 1.45
  },
  {
    "text": "the steps I took to do it.",
    "start": 454.979,
    "duration": 2.458
  },
  {
    "text": "I want to share three of them with you.",
    "start": 458.093,
    "duration": 3.401
  },
  {
    "text": "The first",
    "start": 461.518,
    "duration": 2.074
  },
  {
    "text": "was to be guided by principles.",
    "start": 465.383,
    "duration": 2.1
  },
  {
    "text": "Because I realized",
    "start": 468.426,
    "duration": 1.178
  },
  {
    "text": "that in the midst of panic\nand mental block,",
    "start": 469.628,
    "duration": 2.816
  },
  {
    "text": "if I followed my principles,",
    "start": 473.309,
    "duration": 3.301
  },
  {
    "text": "I acted correctly.",
    "start": 476.634,
    "duration": 1.679
  },
  {
    "text": "I remember the first night",
    "start": 480.265,
    "duration": 3.171
  },
  {
    "text": "in a concentration camp\nthat the guerrillas had built",
    "start": 483.46,
    "duration": 3.848
  },
  {
    "text": "in the middle of the jungle,",
    "start": 487.332,
    "duration": 1.338
  },
  {
    "text": "with 12-foot-high bars,",
    "start": 489.448,
    "duration": 3.354
  },
  {
    "text": "barbed wire,",
    "start": 492.826,
    "duration": 1.605
  },
  {
    "text": "lookouts in the four corners",
    "start": 494.455,
    "duration": 2.34
  },
  {
    "text": "and armed men pointing\nguns at us 24 hours a day.",
    "start": 496.819,
    "duration": 3.372
  },
  {
    "text": "That morning, the first morning,",
    "start": 501.318,
    "duration": 2.161
  },
  {
    "text": "some men arrived, yelling:",
    "start": 504.678,
    "duration": 2.707
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Count off! Count off!\"",
    "start": 507.409,
    "duration": 1.833
  },
  {
    "text": "My fellow hostages woke up, startled,",
    "start": 510.567,
    "duration": 4.179
  },
  {
    "text": "and began to identify themselves\nin numbered sequence.",
    "start": 514.77,
    "duration": 3.328
  },
  {
    "text": "But when it was my turn,",
    "start": 518.637,
    "duration": 1.651
  },
  {
    "text": "I said,",
    "start": 521.732,
    "duration": 1.153
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Ingrid Betancourt.",
    "start": 523.858,
    "duration": 1.345
  },
  {
    "text": "If you want to know if I'm here,\ncall me by my name.\"",
    "start": 525.227,
    "duration": 3.038
  },
  {
    "text": "The guards' fury",
    "start": 529.386,
    "duration": 1.999
  },
  {
    "text": "was nothing compared\nto that of the other hostages,",
    "start": 532.669,
    "duration": 2.468
  },
  {
    "text": "because, obviously they were scared --",
    "start": 535.84,
    "duration": 3.075
  },
  {
    "text": "we were all scared --",
    "start": 538.939,
    "duration": 1.409
  },
  {
    "text": "and they were afraid that, because of me,\nthey would be punished.",
    "start": 540.372,
    "duration": 3.41
  },
  {
    "text": "But for me,",
    "start": 544.476,
    "duration": 1.271
  },
  {
    "text": "beyond fear was the need\nto defend my identity,",
    "start": 545.771,
    "duration": 6.661
  },
  {
    "text": "to not let them turn me into\na thing or a number.",
    "start": 552.456,
    "duration": 3.547
  },
  {
    "text": "That was one of the principles:",
    "start": 556.027,
    "duration": 1.57
  },
  {
    "text": "to defend",
    "start": 558.138,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "what I considered to be human dignity.",
    "start": 561.416,
    "duration": 2.44
  },
  {
    "text": "But make no mistake:",
    "start": 565.277,
    "duration": 1.903
  },
  {
    "text": "the guerrillas had it all",
    "start": 567.204,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "very well analyzed --",
    "start": 570.534,
    "duration": 1.647
  },
  {
    "text": "they had been kidnapping for years,",
    "start": 572.205,
    "duration": 2.191
  },
  {
    "text": "and they had developed a technique",
    "start": 574.42,
    "duration": 3.477
  },
  {
    "text": "to break us,",
    "start": 578.865,
    "duration": 1.605
  },
  {
    "text": "to defeat us, to divide us.",
    "start": 580.494,
    "duration": 1.76
  },
  {
    "text": "And so,",
    "start": 582.835,
    "duration": 1.227
  },
  {
    "text": "the second step",
    "start": 584.708,
    "duration": 1.662
  },
  {
    "text": "was to learn how to build\nsupportive trust,",
    "start": 587.977,
    "duration": 3.007
  },
  {
    "text": "to learn how to unite.",
    "start": 591.008,
    "duration": 2.404
  },
  {
    "text": "The jungle is like a different planet.",
    "start": 595.268,
    "duration": 3.083
  },
  {
    "text": "It's a world",
    "start": 599.533,
    "duration": 2.585
  },
  {
    "text": "of shadows, of rain,",
    "start": 604.023,
    "duration": 2.343
  },
  {
    "text": "with the hum of millions of bugs --",
    "start": 607.937,
    "duration": 4.59
  },
  {
    "text": "maji√±a ants, bullet ants.",
    "start": 612.551,
    "duration": 2.205
  },
  {
    "text": "I didn't stop scratching a single day\nwhile I was in the jungle.",
    "start": 615.496,
    "duration": 3.275
  },
  {
    "text": "And of course, there were tarantulas,\nscorpions, anacondas ...",
    "start": 621.032,
    "duration": 4.587
  },
  {
    "text": "I once came face to face\nwith a 24-foot long anaconda",
    "start": 625.643,
    "duration": 4.203
  },
  {
    "text": "that could have swallowed me in one bite.",
    "start": 629.87,
    "duration": 2.154
  },
  {
    "text": "Jaguars ...",
    "start": 632.048,
    "duration": 1.182
  },
  {
    "text": "But I want to tell you",
    "start": 633.921,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "that none of these animals\ndid us as much harm",
    "start": 635.945,
    "duration": 4.047
  },
  {
    "text": "as the human beings.",
    "start": 640.741,
    "duration": 1.317
  },
  {
    "text": "The guerrillas terrorized us.",
    "start": 646.979,
    "duration": 2.226
  },
  {
    "text": "They spread rumors.",
    "start": 649.665,
    "duration": 3.183
  },
  {
    "text": "Among the hostages,\nthey sparked betrayals,",
    "start": 653.514,
    "duration": 2.894
  },
  {
    "text": "jealousy,",
    "start": 657.087,
    "duration": 1.468
  },
  {
    "text": "resentment,",
    "start": 659.111,
    "duration": 1.293
  },
  {
    "text": "mistrust.",
    "start": 661.135,
    "duration": 1.251
  },
  {
    "text": "The first time I escaped\nfor a long time was with Lucho.",
    "start": 663.595,
    "duration": 6.474
  },
  {
    "text": "Lucho had been a hostage\nfor two years longer than I had.",
    "start": 670.093,
    "duration": 2.809
  },
  {
    "text": "We decided to tie ourselves up",
    "start": 673.557,
    "duration": 3.032
  },
  {
    "text": "with ropes",
    "start": 677.51,
    "duration": 1.647
  },
  {
    "text": "to have the strength\nto lower ourselves into that dark water",
    "start": 679.181,
    "duration": 4.417
  },
  {
    "text": "full of piranhas and alligators.",
    "start": 683.622,
    "duration": 3.024
  },
  {
    "text": "What we did was, during the day,\nwe would hide in the mangroves.",
    "start": 688.271,
    "duration": 4.471
  },
  {
    "text": "And at night,",
    "start": 693.702,
    "duration": 1.667
  },
  {
    "text": "we would leave, get in the water,",
    "start": 695.393,
    "duration": 2.053
  },
  {
    "text": "and we would swim\nand let the current carry us.",
    "start": 698.377,
    "duration": 3.235
  },
  {
    "text": "That went on for several days.",
    "start": 702.778,
    "duration": 2.194
  },
  {
    "text": "But Lucho",
    "start": 705.615,
    "duration": 1.777
  },
  {
    "text": "became sick.",
    "start": 709.004,
    "duration": 1.358
  },
  {
    "text": "He was diabetic,",
    "start": 710.386,
    "duration": 1.314
  },
  {
    "text": "and he fell into a diabetic coma.",
    "start": 712.41,
    "duration": 1.679
  },
  {
    "text": "So the guerrillas captured us.",
    "start": 715.148,
    "duration": 4.208
  },
  {
    "text": "But after having lived\nthrough that with Lucho,",
    "start": 720.618,
    "duration": 3.221
  },
  {
    "text": "after having faced fear together, united,",
    "start": 724.702,
    "duration": 2.676
  },
  {
    "text": "not punishment, not violence -- nothing --",
    "start": 728.371,
    "duration": 3.548
  },
  {
    "text": "could ever again divide us.",
    "start": 732.711,
    "duration": 3.314
  },
  {
    "text": "What's certain is,",
    "start": 739.128,
    "duration": 1.786
  },
  {
    "text": "all the guerrillas' manipulation\nwas so damaging to us",
    "start": 740.938,
    "duration": 3.796
  },
  {
    "text": "that even today,",
    "start": 746.057,
    "duration": 1.782
  },
  {
    "text": "among some of the hostages",
    "start": 748.888,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "from back then,",
    "start": 752.586,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "tensions linger,",
    "start": 755.531,
    "duration": 1.565
  },
  {
    "text": "passed down from all that poison",
    "start": 758.104,
    "duration": 3.475
  },
  {
    "text": "that the guerrillas created.",
    "start": 763.586,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "The third step",
    "start": 767.745,
    "duration": 1.302
  },
  {
    "text": "is very important to me,",
    "start": 770.459,
    "duration": 2.397
  },
  {
    "text": "and it's a gift\nthat I want to give to you.",
    "start": 772.88,
    "duration": 2.36
  },
  {
    "text": "The third step is to learn\nhow to develop faith.",
    "start": 776.163,
    "duration": 4.562
  },
  {
    "text": "I want to explain it like this:",
    "start": 782.994,
    "duration": 3.767
  },
  {
    "text": "Jhon Frank Pinchao",
    "start": 787.61,
    "duration": 1.455
  },
  {
    "text": "was a police officer",
    "start": 789.929,
    "duration": 2.328
  },
  {
    "text": "who had been a hostage\nfor more than eight years.",
    "start": 792.281,
    "duration": 2.42
  },
  {
    "text": "He was famous for being\nthe biggest scaredy-cat of us all.",
    "start": 795.385,
    "duration": 3.906
  },
  {
    "text": "But Pincho -- I called him \"Pincho\" --",
    "start": 802.163,
    "duration": 2.755
  },
  {
    "text": "Pincho decided that he wanted to escape.",
    "start": 804.942,
    "duration": 4.655
  },
  {
    "text": "And he asked me to help him.",
    "start": 810.192,
    "duration": 1.363
  },
  {
    "text": "By that point, I basically had\na master's degree in escape attempts.",
    "start": 811.579,
    "duration": 3.505
  },
  {
    "text": "(Laughter)",
    "start": 815.108,
    "duration": 1.425
  },
  {
    "text": "So",
    "start": 817.012,
    "duration": 1.232
  },
  {
    "text": "we got started but we had a delay,",
    "start": 820.014,
    "duration": 1.735
  },
  {
    "text": "because first, Pincho\nhad to learn how to swim.",
    "start": 821.773,
    "duration": 2.659
  },
  {
    "text": "And we had to carry out\nall these preparations in total secrecy.",
    "start": 825.257,
    "duration": 4.892
  },
  {
    "text": "Anyway, when we finally\nhad everything ready,",
    "start": 830.855,
    "duration": 3.378
  },
  {
    "text": "Pincho came up to me\none afternoon and said,",
    "start": 834.257,
    "duration": 4.17
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Ingrid, suppose I'm in the jungle,",
    "start": 838.451,
    "duration": 3.159
  },
  {
    "text": "and I go around and around in circles,\nand I can't find the way out.",
    "start": 841.634,
    "duration": 3.621
  },
  {
    "text": "What do I do?\"",
    "start": 845.279,
    "duration": 1.17
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Pincho,",
    "start": 847.846,
    "duration": 1.177
  },
  {
    "text": "you grab a phone,",
    "start": 850.571,
    "duration": 1.307
  },
  {
    "text": "and you call the man upstairs.\"",
    "start": 853.06,
    "duration": 1.619
  },
  {
    "text": "\"Ingrid, you know I don't believe in God.\"",
    "start": 855.831,
    "duration": 3.127
  },
  {
    "text": "\"God doesn't care. He'll still help you.\"",
    "start": 863.577,
    "duration": 2.709
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 869.079,
    "duration": 3.098
  },
  {
    "text": "It rained all night that night.",
    "start": 875.447,
    "duration": 2.521
  },
  {
    "text": "The following morning,",
    "start": 879.024,
    "duration": 1.481
  },
  {
    "text": "the camp woke up to a big commotion,",
    "start": 881.738,
    "duration": 2.075
  },
  {
    "text": "because Pincho had fled.",
    "start": 883.837,
    "duration": 2.684
  },
  {
    "text": "They made us dismantle the camp,\nand we started marching.",
    "start": 886.545,
    "duration": 2.761
  },
  {
    "text": "During the march,",
    "start": 889.33,
    "duration": 1.263
  },
  {
    "text": "the head guerrillas told us\nthat Pincho had died,",
    "start": 892.149,
    "duration": 4.556
  },
  {
    "text": "and that they had found his remains",
    "start": 896.729,
    "duration": 3.135
  },
  {
    "text": "eaten by an anaconda.",
    "start": 899.888,
    "duration": 1.531
  },
  {
    "text": "Seventeen days passed --",
    "start": 904.379,
    "duration": 1.694
  },
  {
    "text": "and believe me, I counted them,\nbecause they were torture for me.",
    "start": 906.097,
    "duration": 5.351
  },
  {
    "text": "But on the seventeenth day,",
    "start": 913.98,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "the news exploded from the radio:",
    "start": 918.003,
    "duration": 1.916
  },
  {
    "text": "Pincho was free and obviously alive.",
    "start": 919.943,
    "duration": 3.214
  },
  {
    "text": "And this was the first thing he said:",
    "start": 924.024,
    "duration": 3.504
  },
  {
    "text": "\"I know my fellow hostages are listening.",
    "start": 928.872,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "Ingrid,",
    "start": 931.633,
    "duration": 1.494
  },
  {
    "text": "I did what you told me.",
    "start": 933.151,
    "duration": 1.722
  },
  {
    "text": "I called the man upstairs,",
    "start": 934.897,
    "duration": 1.671
  },
  {
    "text": "and he sent me the patrol\nthat rescued me from the jungle.\"",
    "start": 936.592,
    "duration": 3.541
  },
  {
    "text": "That was an extraordinary moment,",
    "start": 943.284,
    "duration": 3.013
  },
  {
    "text": "because ...",
    "start": 946.321,
    "duration": 1.166
  },
  {
    "text": "obviously fear is contagious.",
    "start": 948.098,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "But faith is, too.",
    "start": 950.729,
    "duration": 1.43
  },
  {
    "text": "Faith isn't rational or emotional.",
    "start": 952.183,
    "duration": 2.639
  },
  {
    "text": "Faith",
    "start": 955.631,
    "duration": 1.182
  },
  {
    "text": "is an exercise of the will.",
    "start": 957.86,
    "duration": 2.616
  },
  {
    "text": "It's the discipline of the will.",
    "start": 961.087,
    "duration": 2.634
  },
  {
    "text": "It's what allows us to transform\neverything that we are --",
    "start": 964.173,
    "duration": 3.471
  },
  {
    "text": "our weaknesses, our frailties,",
    "start": 967.668,
    "duration": 2.298
  },
  {
    "text": "into strength, into power.",
    "start": 969.99,
    "duration": 1.59
  },
  {
    "text": "It's truly a transformation.",
    "start": 971.604,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "It's what gives us the strength",
    "start": 974.641,
    "duration": 2.861
  },
  {
    "text": "to stand up",
    "start": 977.526,
    "duration": 1.381
  },
  {
    "text": "in the face of fear",
    "start": 980.264,
    "duration": 1.205
  },
  {
    "text": "look above it,",
    "start": 982.484,
    "duration": 1.724
  },
  {
    "text": "and see beyond it.",
    "start": 984.232,
    "duration": 1.398
  },
  {
    "text": "I hope you remember that,",
    "start": 988.042,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "because I know we all need",
    "start": 991.605,
    "duration": 1.835
  },
  {
    "text": "to connect with that strength\nwe have inside of us",
    "start": 994.463,
    "duration": 2.994
  },
  {
    "text": "for the times when there's a storm\nraging around our boat.",
    "start": 998.057,
    "duration": 4.442
  },
  {
    "text": "Many, many, many, many years passed",
    "start": 1003.26,
    "duration": 4.409
  },
  {
    "text": "before I could return to my house.",
    "start": 1009.399,
    "duration": 4.609
  },
  {
    "text": "But when they took us, handcuffed,\ninto the helicopter",
    "start": 1015.936,
    "duration": 5.029
  },
  {
    "text": "that finally took us out of the jungle,",
    "start": 1020.989,
    "duration": 2.055
  },
  {
    "text": "everything happened as quickly\nas when they kidnapped me.",
    "start": 1023.068,
    "duration": 3.245
  },
  {
    "text": "In an instant,",
    "start": 1027.797,
    "duration": 1.632
  },
  {
    "text": "I saw the guerrilla commander at my feet,",
    "start": 1029.453,
    "duration": 4.023
  },
  {
    "text": "gagged,",
    "start": 1033.5,
    "duration": 1.225
  },
  {
    "text": "and the rescue leader,",
    "start": 1035.566,
    "duration": 2.266
  },
  {
    "text": "yelling:",
    "start": 1039.01,
    "duration": 1.164
  },
  {
    "text": "\"We're the Colombian army!",
    "start": 1040.927,
    "duration": 3.415
  },
  {
    "text": "You are free!\"",
    "start": 1044.367,
    "duration": 2.379
  },
  {
    "text": "The shriek",
    "start": 1048.303,
    "duration": 1.538
  },
  {
    "text": "that came out of all of us",
    "start": 1050.62,
    "duration": 2.072
  },
  {
    "text": "when we regained our freedom,",
    "start": 1052.716,
    "duration": 1.991
  },
  {
    "text": "continues to vibrate in me to this day.",
    "start": 1055.201,
    "duration": 4.571
  },
  {
    "text": "Now,",
    "start": 1062.089,
    "duration": 1.171
  },
  {
    "text": "I know they can divide all of us,",
    "start": 1064.363,
    "duration": 3.207
  },
  {
    "text": "they can manipulate us all with fear.",
    "start": 1067.594,
    "duration": 2.417
  },
  {
    "text": "The \"No\" vote on the peace\nreferendum in Colombia;",
    "start": 1072.646,
    "duration": 4.268
  },
  {
    "text": "Brexit;",
    "start": 1076.938,
    "duration": 1.769
  },
  {
    "text": "the idea of a wall\nbetween Mexico and the United States;",
    "start": 1078.731,
    "duration": 3.747
  },
  {
    "text": "Islamic terrorism --",
    "start": 1083.143,
    "duration": 1.682
  },
  {
    "text": "they're all examples\nof using fear politically",
    "start": 1084.849,
    "duration": 4.297
  },
  {
    "text": "to divide and recruit us.",
    "start": 1089.855,
    "duration": 2.582
  },
  {
    "text": "We all feel fear.",
    "start": 1094.19,
    "duration": 2.0
  },
  {
    "text": "But we can all avoid being recruited",
    "start": 1096.912,
    "duration": 3.367
  },
  {
    "text": "using the resources we have --\nour principles, unity, faith.",
    "start": 1101.254,
    "duration": 5.112
  },
  {
    "text": "Yes, fear is part of the human condition,",
    "start": 1107.659,
    "duration": 3.608
  },
  {
    "text": "as well as being necessary for survival.",
    "start": 1111.291,
    "duration": 3.279
  },
  {
    "text": "But above all,",
    "start": 1115.205,
    "duration": 1.739
  },
  {
    "text": "it's the guide by which each of us builds",
    "start": 1116.968,
    "duration": 4.756
  },
  {
    "text": "our identity, our personality.",
    "start": 1122.574,
    "duration": 3.168
  },
  {
    "text": "It's true, I was 41 years old\nthe first time I felt fear,",
    "start": 1128.649,
    "duration": 6.98
  },
  {
    "text": "and feeling fear was not my decision.",
    "start": 1135.653,
    "duration": 3.58
  },
  {
    "text": "But it was my decision\nwhat to do with that fear.",
    "start": 1140.061,
    "duration": 4.692
  },
  {
    "text": "You can survive",
    "start": 1147.054,
    "duration": 3.412
  },
  {
    "text": "crawling along, fearful.",
    "start": 1151.46,
    "duration": 2.821
  },
  {
    "text": "But you can also",
    "start": 1154.898,
    "duration": 1.48
  },
  {
    "text": "rise above the fear,",
    "start": 1157.847,
    "duration": 2.535
  },
  {
    "text": "rise up, spread your wings,",
    "start": 1160.406,
    "duration": 2.812
  },
  {
    "text": "and soar, fly high, high, high, high,\nuntil you reach the stars,",
    "start": 1163.242,
    "duration": 4.677
  },
  {
    "text": "where all of us want to go.",
    "start": 1167.943,
    "duration": 3.026
  },
  {
    "text": "Thank you.",
    "start": 1173.367,
    "duration": 1.152
  },
  {
    "text": "(Applause)",
    "start": 1174.543,
    "duration": 3.808
  }
]